<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Cable-Tricep-Pushdown">Cable Tricep Pushdown</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/cable-tricep-pushdown" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cable tricep pushdown</a> is an isolation exercise that is used to build and shape stronger-looking triceps. The cable offers a continuous resistance, which is excellent for muscle growth and endurance.</p>



<p>The primary movers are the triceps brachii, and the secondary muscles are the wrist flexors, wrist extensors, and posterior deltoid.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Cable Tricep Pushdown" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/987039381?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Cable Tricep Pushdown Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Adjust the cable to the highest point and attach your rope handle.</li>



<li>Grab the rope, and pull your elbows down to your sides. Your hands should be resting at shoulder height with your elbows bent.</li>



<li>Position your feet shoulder-width apart, and lean forward slightly.</li>



<li>Inhale, and engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale, and push the rope toward the floor until your arms are straight.</li>



<li>Pause briefly, inhale, and allow your elbows to bend, returning the rope to shoulder height.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Lean forward slightly and engage your core. This will help you create a solid base, and improve your ability to isolate the triceps.</li>



<li>Keep your elbows tucked by your side. This will improve tricep isolation.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



